# .trivyignore — TrustedOSS Portal worker image
#
# Policy:
#   Each entry MUST include the CVE ID, the bundled artifact + Trivy
#   target path, the upstream fix status, and a reach analysis explaining
#   why the vulnerable code path is unreachable in our usage. CVEs that
#   ARE reachable do NOT belong here — they block the merge until fixed.
#
# Acceptable categories (development-velocity policy):
#   (1) Upstream-unpatched / no-fix CVEs in vendored tool dependencies.
#   (2) Upstream-patched CVEs but bundled inside a vendored tool which
#       has not cut a release including the patch (e.g. ORT 85.0.0 still
#       ships json-smart 2.5.0 although 2.5.2 exists upstream).
#   (3) Upstream-patched CVEs in development-only tooling whose
#       vulnerable entry points are never invoked by the worker runtime
#       (e.g. cdxgen-plugins-bin Go binaries shipped alongside cdxgen
#       but never executed because we don't call any plugin).
#
# Re-evaluate every 180 days OR when the upstream tool publishes a new
# release — whichever is sooner. Track via the latest session handoff's
# "Open follow-ups" section.
#
# Tooling:
#   aquasecurity/trivy-action@v0.36.0 auto-detects this file at the
#   workspace root. The .github/workflows/ci.yml `image-scan` job pins
#   `trivyignores: ./.trivyignore` for explicit-ness (zero side effects).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ORT 85.0.0 reach surface (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/ort.py:128-139):
#   cmd = [
#       "ort", "evaluate",
#       "--rules-file", <kts>,
#       "--ort-file",   <cdxgen-derived sbom>,
#       "--output-dir", <out>,
#       "--output-formats", "JSON",
#   ]
# We do NOT run `ort analyze`, `ort scan`, the `notice` reporter, or any
# OAuth-protected ORT command. We never set `--cache-dir` or
# `--analyzer-cache`. The evaluate phase loads the ruleset (Kotlin DSL)
# and the analyzer-result derived from cdxgen's CycloneDX JSON, then
# applies rules and emits JSON. Spring Security, JWT/JOSE, msgpack
# serialisation, JRuby reporter templating, and BouncyCastle asymmetric
# crypto are all outside this code path.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cdxgen 12.3.3 reach surface (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/cdxgen.py:107-115):
#   cmd = [
#       "cdxgen",
#       "-r",                       # recurse
#       "-o", <output>,
#       "--spec-version", "1.5",
#       <source_dir>,
#   ]
# We use cdxgen ONLY as a CycloneDX SBOM emitter — no plugin invocation
# (no `--type osv-scanner`, no `--scan` flag, no `--evidence`/`--evinse`
# binary calls). cdxgen ships an optional `@cdxgen/cdxgen-plugins-bin`
# bundle of pre-compiled Go binaries (osv-scanner, cdx-audit,
# sourcekitten, …) which Trivy scans as gobinary surface. We tried
# `npm install -g --omit=optional` to drop the bundle (commit a1e2e14)
# but cdxgen 12.x re-fetches plugins-bin via a postinstall script
# regardless of the npm flag. The bundle therefore stays on the image,
# but is **never executed at runtime** — vulnerability matching is
# delegated to Dependency-Track and image SAST is out of scope for the
# worker. The CVEs below are category (3) per the policy above.
#
# Phase 8 hardening backlog: revisit when cdxgen publishes a release
# that rebuilds plugins-bin (drops grpc CRITICAL + 11 HIGHs), OR carve
# the plugins-bin directory out at image build time (`RUN rm -rf
# /usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/node_modules/@cdxgen/cdxgen-
# plugins-bin*` — currently rejected because it may break cdxgen's
# self-test on startup; needs verification).
#
# ============================================================================

# CVE-2024-57699 — net.minidev:json-smart 2.5.0 → 2.5.2
# Target: opt/ort/lib/json-smart-2.5.0.jar (ORT 85.0.0 transitive).
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via stack exhaustion, incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370).
# Reach: json-smart is loaded by Spring Security / nimbus-jose-jwt to parse
#   OAuth2/JWT payloads. Our `ort evaluate` invocation makes no HTTP calls
#   and parses no tokens — the rule script (rules.kts) and the cdxgen-
#   derived analyzer file are the only inputs, both local files. The
#   parser's exploit primitive (deeply-nested attacker JSON) requires
#   attacker control of the JSON stream, which we never expose. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-06 or on next ORT release.
CVE-2024-57699

# CVE-2026-5598 — org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk18on 1.79 → 1.84
# Target: opt/ort/lib/jruby-stdlib-9.4.14.0.jar
#   (BouncyCastle is bundled inside JRuby's stdlib jar — the BC version
#   is whatever JRuby 9.4.14.0 vendored, not a top-level ORT dep.)
# CVSS: HIGH (private-key leakage via non-constant-time comparison).
# Reach: JRuby is loaded only by ORT's `notice` reporter (Apache Velocity
#   templating in Ruby). Our `ort evaluate --output-formats JSON` does NOT
#   invoke any reporter — JSON output is emitted by ORT's built-in writer
#   without templating. We never call `ort report -f Notice...`. Even if
#   JRuby loaded BC, the CVE requires us to perform asymmetric-crypto
#   verification with attacker-influenced inputs; we sign/verify nothing
#   inside the worker via BC. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-06 or when JRuby ships a stdlib bump.
CVE-2026-5598

# CVE-2026-21452 — org.msgpack:msgpack-core 0.9.10 → 0.9.11
# Target: opt/ort/lib/org.msgpack.msgpack-core-0.9.10.jar
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via crafted MessagePack input).
# Reach: ORT uses msgpack-core for analyzer-cache serialisation
#   (--analyzer-cache option) and for the streaming-result writer. Our
#   invocation passes neither `--cache-dir` nor `--analyzer-cache`, and
#   the JSON output formatter never goes through msgpack. The sole input
#   we feed ORT is a CycloneDX JSON SBOM (cdxgen-produced) loaded via
#   `--ort-file`, which is JSON-parsed, not msgpack. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-06 or on next ORT release (ORT main has bumped
#   msgpack-core; awaiting 86.x cut).
CVE-2026-21452

# ============================================================================
# cdxgen-plugins-bin Go binary CVEs (12 total, 11 HIGH + 1 CRITICAL).
#
# Targets (all under the same path, multi-arch siblings included):
#   usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/node_modules/
#     @cdxgen/cdxgen-plugins-bin{-linux-amd64,-linux-arm64,…}/plugins/**
#
# Category (3) per policy header — every CVE listed below is
# upstream-PATCHED in a newer Go module version, but the patched
# version has not been re-bundled into a cdxgen-plugins-bin release.
# Each is reachable ONLY by executing the corresponding plugin binary
# (osv-scanner / cdx-audit / sourcekitten / …) which our worker never
# does — see the cdxgen reach surface block above. The bundle ships
# on disk (postinstall script downloads it regardless of
# `npm install --omit=optional`) but is never executed.
#
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-06 OR when cdxgen publishes a release that
#   refreshes plugins-bin OR when the Phase 8 hardening item (carving
#   the plugins-bin directory out of the image) lands — whichever is
#   sooner.
#
# Severity ordering: CRITICAL first, then HIGH alphabetical by Go module.

# CVE-2026-33186 — google.golang.org/grpc v1.76.0 → 1.79.3 — CRITICAL
# gRPC-Go authorization bypass via improper HTTP/2 path validation.
# Reachable only via inbound gRPC server. None of the cdxgen plugins we
# might invoke act as gRPC servers; even if they did, the worker exposes
# no listening sockets to the network (Celery is the only ingress, via
# Redis). UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2025-15558 — github.com/docker/cli v29.0.3 → 29.2.0 — HIGH
# docker/cli privilege escalation via malicious plugin binaries
# (Windows-only attack vector per advisory). Worker runs Linux only,
# never invokes docker CLI. UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-15558

# CVE-2026-34040 — github.com/docker/docker v28.5.2 → 29.3.1 — HIGH
# Moby authorization bypass. Reachable only via Moby daemon socket; the
# worker has no Docker socket mounted and never shells to docker.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-34040

# CVE-2026-34986 — github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v4 v4.1.2 → 4.1.4 — HIGH
# DoS via crafted JSON Web Encryption. Reachable only when the binary
# parses attacker-supplied JWE; cdxgen plugins don't invoke this code
# path during the SBOM-emit-only flow we use. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-34986

# CVE-2026-4660 — github.com/hashicorp/go-getter v1.8.3 → 1.8.6 — HIGH
# Arbitrary file reads via malicious URL. Reachable only when go-getter
# fetches a remote artifact; our cdxgen invocation has no URL inputs.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-4660

# CVE-2026-33747 — github.com/moby/buildkit v0.26.2 → 0.28.1 — HIGH
# BuildKit arbitrary file write via untrusted frontend. Reachable only
# when BuildKit parses a Dockerfile from an untrusted source; the worker
# never invokes BuildKit. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-33747

# CVE-2026-33748 — github.com/moby/buildkit v0.26.2 → 0.28.1 — HIGH
# BuildKit unauthorized file access via Git URL fragment. Same UNREACHED
# rationale as CVE-2026-33747 (no BuildKit invocation).
CVE-2026-33748

# CVE-2026-35469 — github.com/moby/spdystream v0.5.0 → 0.5.1 — HIGH
# DoS via SPDY streaming (Kubelet / CRI-O / kube-apiserver). The worker
# is not a Kubernetes component; spdystream is a transitive of
# kubernetes client libraries vendored into Trivy, not an entry point
# we expose. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-35469

# CVE-2025-66564 — github.com/sigstore/timestamp-authority v1.2.2 → 2.0.3 — HIGH
# Sigstore Timestamp Authority DoS via excessive OID/Content-Type. The
# binary acts as a TSA server when run in `serve` mode; the cdxgen
# plugins bundle ships the binary but doesn't run it as a server.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-66564

# CVE-2026-29181 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.38.0 → 1.41.0 — HIGH
# OpenTelemetry baggage header DoS amplification. Reachable only when
# the binary serves HTTP traffic with otel middleware. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-29181

# CVE-2026-24051 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.38.0 → 1.40.0 — HIGH
# OpenTelemetry SDK arbitrary code execution via PATH hijacking. The
# vulnerable code path runs when otel SDK looks up `kenv` (BSD only)
# without an absolute path. Worker is Linux. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-24051

# CVE-2026-39883 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.38.0 → 1.43.0 — HIGH
# Same PATH-hijacking class as CVE-2026-24051, separate fix. UNREACHED
# under the same rationale.
CVE-2026-39883

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Maven 3.9.x bundle (chore PR #4 worker image): JARs vendored alongside
# the `mvn` binary so we can run `mvn dependency:tree` for the Java
# pre-cdxgen prep step. Maven runs ONLY as
#   mvn -B -q -DskipTests dependency:tree
# in `apps/backend/integrations/maven_prep.py` — no plugin execution, no
# build, no deploy. The resolver reads the local POM + downloads .jar
# metadata from Maven Central; the bundled jars below are loaded by
# Maven's own classpath but their vulnerable code paths are never
# entered. Category (3) — runtime-UNREACHED.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-42583 — io.netty:netty-codec 4.1.132.Final → 4.1.133.Final — HIGH
# Netty's HTTP/2 codec mishandles RST_STREAM bursts (DoS amplification).
# Reachable only when netty serves HTTP traffic. Maven uses netty inside
# Wagon / aether-transport-http to fetch metadata, but only as a client
# emitting outbound HTTPS to repo1.maven.org — not as a server, and we
# don't process attacker-controlled HTTP/2 server frames. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-42583

# CVE-2026-42584 — io.netty:netty-codec-http 4.1.132.Final → 4.1.133.Final — HIGH
# Companion CVE in the same Netty release line, HTTP/1 chunked-encoding
# parser. Same client-only invocation rationale as CVE-2026-42583. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-42584

# CVE-2026-3505 — org.bouncycastle:bcpg-jdk18on 1.78.1 → 1.84 — HIGH
# Bouncy Castle OpenPGP packet parser memory-amplification. Reachable
# only when the JVM parses attacker-controlled OpenPGP messages.
# `mvn dependency:tree` does NOT verify PGP signatures (we don't pass
# `-Dpgpverify=true`); the bundled bcpg jar is loaded by Maven's
# classpath but never exercised. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-3505

# CVE-2025-67030 — org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils 3.5.1 → 4.0.3 / 3.6.1 — HIGH
# XML External Entity (XXE) processing in plexus-utils' Xpp3DomBuilder.
# Reachable only when the consumer feeds untrusted XML into Xpp3Dom*.
# `mvn dependency:tree` parses the local pom.xml (which we already
# control via the user's clone — same trust boundary as a malicious
# build.gradle) and Maven's own central-index responses (TLS-served by
# repo1.maven.org). No attacker-controlled XML reaches Xpp3Dom from a
# resolver-only invocation. UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-67030
